[The term 'HPAI' (highly pathogenic avian influenza) relates to the assessment of the virus's virulence in chickens; see updated text in section "B. Diagnostic techniques 2. Assessment of pathogenicity", of OIE's Manual, Chapter 2.3.4. -- Avian influenza, at http://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/eng/Health_standards/tahm/2.03.04_AI.pdf.

So far, the current HPAI H5N8 epizootic in South Korea has affected duck farms only, causing -- as expected -- minimal rates of morbidity and mortality. Much higher rates might be expected if/when the virus penetrates into chicken flocks. - Mod.AS

Maps of South Korea can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/maps/korea-south-admin-map.jpg and http://healthmap.org/r/9P-q. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
